The paper deals with human pose estimation from images using deep Convolutional Neural Network (ConvNet), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel framework for 3D pose inference, which involves training a ConvNet with two branches and a deep regression network, indicating a possible focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of an annotation user interface, which suggests a potential interest in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
